Re: Bugfixes in SVN rev 130

Bitcointalk

2010-08-13 03:15:23 UTC - [11]Original Post

   No, thatʼs not what it is.
   -paytxfee allows you to include a transaction fee with your
   transactions.  If transaction confirmations become slow, you can get
   priority by using "-paytxfee=0.01".  Any transactions you send would
   cost an extra 0.01.  Thereʼs no reason to use more than 0.01.
   Itʼs just there in case we need it.  It probably wonʼt be needed, and
   it can be explained more if we do.
